    "body": "okay, so after some more testing and commenting out the transient prompt stuff, I've found a bit more information about what is happening, both with and without the transient prompt.\n\nOkay, so with my transient prompt implementation enabled, the normal status widget seems to not work properly as well as any custom.* modules that reference `$?` or `$status`. With transient prompt implementation commented out, the normal status widget does work as intended, but the custom modules that reference `$?` or `$status` still don't work, and I've tested this in both the default and right prompts, shown below.\n\nhere shown is multiple commands run using a custom module in main and right prompts using the command `echo $status`, reporting a value of 0 for all of it, even when the status module reports the correct status code \n<img width=\"1259\" height=\"228\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1057b8f5-156d-4691-a207-4bbf617fc5ac\" />\n\nNow the only downside of all of this is that I've come to realize I can't reopen the issue myself, and it definitely seems to be an issue with starship",
